<Base title="start">
  <p class="opener"><strong>yo dawg</strong>, i heard you like 1337 skills, so we put 1337 skills in your 1337 coding agent so you can 1337 while claude code 1337s.</p>

  <p>best-in-class tooling, practices, and learnings from industry leaders and master craftsmen.</p>

  <pre><code>/plugin marketplace add yzavyas/claude-1337
/plugin install core-1337@claude-1337</code></pre>

  <h2>plugins</h2>

  <ul class="plugin-list">
    <li><a href="/claude-1337/reference/terminal-1337/">terminal-1337</a> — rg, fd, bat, eza, xh, jq</li>
    <li><a href="/claude-1337/reference/rust-1337/">rust-1337</a> — crate decisions from production</li>
    <li><a href="/claude-1337/reference/1337-skill-creator/">1337-skill-creator</a> — build skills with best-in-class answers</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>the problem</h2>

  <p>claude code skills activate ~20% of the time. you install them, ask a relevant question, and claude ignores them.</p>

  <div class="stats">
    <div>
      <div class="stat-value bad">20%</div>
      <div class="stat-label">baseline</div>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="stat-value good">84%</div>
      <div class="stat-label">with fix</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>we researched why and built a fix. <a href="/claude-1337/explanation/">read more</a></p>

  <h2>philosophy</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>learn from masters</strong> — domain experts, maintainers, reputable blogs</li>
    <li><strong>best-in-class only</strong> — "use tokio" not "options include tokio, async-std, smol"</li>
    <li><strong>evidence over stars</strong> — what ripgrep, servo, cloudflare actually use</li>
    <li><strong>skip training knowledge</strong> — only add what claude doesn't know</li>
  </ul>

